Combine chicken and marinade; cover. Refrigerate until ready to grill. Heat grill. In a medium bowl combine salsa, cilantro and banana. Refrigerate until serving time. When ready to grill, place the chicken over medium heat; cover. Cook for 15 to 20 minutes, turning once, until chicken is no longer pink. Brush frequently with marinade during the first 10 minutes of cooking. Serve with salsa.